content:
SIM card invalid having worked for first two weeks.  

- Pixel 4 unlocked, five months old;
- Used Optus on new phone for first three months.  Changed to Telstra with new SIM.  Worked for two weeks and then says invalid, emergency calls only;
- Occasionally the SIM works for about an hour;
- Telstra SIM works in another phone;
- Telstra service verified SIM card is operating correctly;
- An Optus SIM works in my phone;
- SIM and slot inspected, cleaned.  Cache cleared.  Factory reset, still no good.  
- Unable to manually connect to a network in settings since SIM is not detected.

Appears to be a phone issue connecting to Telstra.  Any advice please?
